commit.message: API Change, Logger: adding logger name in case there are multiple loggers running at the same time in parallel and showing in console, to avoid ambiguity in the screen displayed logs.
Minor change to some log messages.
Scene: fixed crash when defining background
Volume Integrator: fixed regression where the volume integrator was not getting the list of lights from the Surface Integrator during preprocessing
VolumeRegions: Fixed crash when creating a DensityVolumeRegion derived class
Export XML: improving export of boolean parameters, updating Test02 to export XML
Export to XML: not exporting normals when mesh has been auto-smoothed
Export to XML: exporting mesh smoothing
Export to XML: exporting volume integrator
Export to XML: adding function to export directly to file so export memory usage is lower compared to exporting to string
Export to XML: Mesh Object exporting material reference
Export to XML: exporting Film layers
Export ImageOutput to XML
API Change in defineCamera, no need for camera name. Exporting Camera to XML
Export to XML: exporting light name
Export to XML: adding exporting texture name
Changing XML export format (WIP)
Instance export to XML, using object_ref and instance_ref for referenced items
Exporting instances to XML
Export as String: generalizing indent levels
Material: removed the need for element parameter, exporting XML as "shader_node" instead of "list_element"
Params system: fixed regression where defaults for Color and String were not respected
Preparing Container export to XML (WIP)
ClassMeta: Added PARAM_SAVE_VARIABLE to properly save a parameter that comes from a variable modified in run time
Allowing excluding "type" from the parameter export metadata checks.
Preparing Container and ParamMap export to file (WIP)

New Container class, to hold a number of scenes, surface integrators and films, so they can be exported to a file. Adding getName for Scene, SurfaceIntegrator and Film so the obtained scenes, films, etc, from a container can be identified.
SurfaceIntegrators/ImageFilm: moving back AA/Mask params from SurfaceIntegrator to ImageFilm and simplifying code a bit
C API / Scene / Accelerator: exposing full Scene Accelerator parameters in API for more flexible/full control. Checking if Scene Accelerator parameters changed or not. Fixing some log messages.
Test03: adapting to current API
